contentrichtext.text: '''F22''', '''F-22''', '''F 22''' or '''F.XXII''' may refer to: * [[Lockheed Martin F-22 Raptor]], an American stealth fighter aircraft ** Video games based on the fighter: *** [[F-22 (series)|''F-22'' (series)]], a series of computer games by Novalogic **** ''[[F-22 Lightning II]]'', a 1996 video game **** [[F-22 Raptor (video game)|''F-22 Raptor'' (video game)]], a 1998 video game **** ''[[F-22 Lightning 3]]'', a 1999 video game *** ''[[F-22: Air Dominance Fighter]]'', a 1997 video game by Digital Image Design *** ''[[F-22 Interceptor]]'', a 1991 video game by Electronic Arts for the Sega Mega Drive/Genesis *** ''[[F-22 Total Air War]]'', a 1998 computer game from Infogrames for Windows 95 * [[76 mm divisional gun M1936 (F-22)]], a Soviet 76.2-mm divisional gun of the World War II era * [[F-22 (psychedelic)]], a drug * [[Fokker F.XXII]], a 1935 Dutch four-engined 22-passenger airliner * [[General Avia F 22]], a 1998 Italian two-seat monoplane * {{HMS|Jackal|F22}}, a 1938 British Royal Navy J-class destroyer * [[PRR F22]], an American * [[F 22 Kongo]], a Swedish air force squadron participating in the United nations peace-keeping operations in Congo 1961-64 * [[F-22P Zulfiquar class frigate]] of the [[Pakistan Navy]] * {{f/}}22, the [[F-number]] measure of photographic lens' [[aperture]] size related to its [[focal length]] and also : * [[VF-22 Sturmvogel II]], a fictional aircraft from the Macross anime series * the [[ICD-10 Chapter V: Mental and behavioural disorders|ICD-10]] code for ''persistent delusional disorders'' {{Letter-NumberCombDisambig}} [[奇幻自衛隊|奇幻自衛隊]]
